reviews.review_text: ARE YOU KIDDING ME Sorry for the CAPS.........  could not help it. This show did not sound this the day they played.OMG I very rarely say that about any show.I will say it again OMG   this is remastered.  Anyone who comes upon this review grab it trust me.    I think this is the first time I have ever giving 5 stars here. First of all seeing them in the city of sin.. but to this good. Listen to phil drop the bombs during scarlet.

Ahh - The Aladdin This was the show I lost my shit at. The scene out front of the Aladdin that day, before the show, was nuts.  Betty Boop blotter was generously handed out. Did one hit too many ...  Ended up being the "Hell Trip" with Jerry turning into a scary looking 'bot.  It was boiling hot, and the subterranean venue was a trip.  Dudes with tatooed snakes on their faces wandered around the casino as the show went on.  The funniest thing I remember after pulling it together, was the deadheads (all tripping -or so I thought) streaming out of the auditorium and playing the blackjack tables.  One dude started winning like crazy and was throwing handfulls of chips into the deadhead crowd.  We all started playing with his chips and drinking free, ice-cold Heinekens (as long as we played).  Hilarious, trippy, scary and memorable.  Thanks for the show Charlie
83 dead Good show.very easy to listen to.i get into the feel of this show very good.
Friend of the Devil wow... Jerry's solo... just beautiful... this is a wonderful recording...

Pretty good show in retrospect Seeing the Dead in Vegas was completely absurd.  There was only a bit of nervous vending and such in the parking lot due to police presence, and dancing in the theatre was prohibited.  Brother Essau was a train wreck and the first set was pretty chaotic in general, but the second set was pretty good.  But what I remember most of all, all these years later, was the ridiculous leisure suite which Phil was wearing, made even more silly because he was so over-weight and bloated back in those days.  Or maybe I was tripping my balls off and imagined the whole thing.

Old skool Dead and Vegas Back in 1983 Las Vegas was almost a dumpy little town out in the Nevada desert. I recall taking Southwest Air hopper flights to/from Phoenix the day of the show. We stayed in the Aladdin. What a strange scene for the Dead. All afternoon and into the night "paging Mr. Jack Straw, Mr Jack Straw to the white courtesy phone please", "Paging Mickey Hart, Mickey Hart to the white courtesy phone please"! Every band member, every character from Dead songs you could imagine was being paged- I do recall "Stella Blue, Miss Stella Blue", and an echo from the past, "paging Mountain Girl, Miss Mountain Girl". It really was entertaining!

At the beginning of my night I was at the door to the theater about 5 persons from the front and we had a discussion with the 30 something security guard before he let us in. "Is it sold out tonight?"-"Yes". "Are we the rowdiest crowd ever for this theatre?" 
"Are you kidding- we had Van Halen in here last week, their fans destroyed a bunch of stuff, you folks seem much more mellow than that." So funny. As a result of being close to the front of the line, once we were allowed in I was forced into an area on the floor which wasn't near my ticket.
Six years is  along time for a project, but having been there, I can say kudos to Charlie are warranted.
